BUGS FOUND AND FIXED (chronological)
========================================================================

1. MPAS REMAP CELL ID MISMATCH [FIXED, BUT IDENTITY PATH TAKEN]
   - Fix: gcol_to_ocean_col prefix-sum mapping added.
   - However, map file has n_a = N_total so identity branch is used.
   - Fix is still correct as defensive code for masked SCRIP maps.

2. frac_b PIO READ CORRUPTION [FIXED]
   - Was: reading frac_b from map file via PIO corrupted shared state.
   - Fix: compute frac_b as sum of CRS row weights in build_comm.

3. MPI BUFFER SAFETY [FIXED]
   - Was: land-only processors had n_send/n_recv=0, passing unallocated
     arrays to MPI_Alltoallv.
   - Fix: allocate buffers to max(1, needed) unconditionally.

4. EAM FILL VALUE LEAKAGE THROUGH REMAP [FIXED]
   - Was: vcoarsen fill values (1e+20) at high-elevation columns passed
     through SpMV because fill_thresh was 1e+30 (too high to catch 1e+20).
     Visible as T_1..T_8 min values of 37-110K (garbage from fill-value
     contamination of the weighted average).
   - Fix: lower fill_thresh from 1e+30 to 1e+10 in horiz_remap_mod.F90.
     No geophysical quantity exceeds 1e+10.

5. MPAS PIO TYPE MISMATCH [FIXED] — ROOT CAUSE OF ALL REMAPPED GARBAGE
   - Was: pio_initdecomp(PIO_REAL) created a float32 decomposition, but
     pio_write_darray received real(r8) (float64) data. PIO interpreted
     8-byte elements as two 4-byte elements, interleaving valid values
     with garbage throughout the output file.
   - Diagnosis: debug log showed correct send buffer values (SST ~24C)
     and zero SpMV output on rank 0 (expected — South Pole land).
     Remapped file showed alternating valid/garbage float32 values:
     [-1.42e+36, -1.906, 1.47e-30, -1.905, ...] — classic double-to-
     single reinterpretation pattern.
   - Fix: convert fld_out to real(4) before pio_write_darray in both
     mpas_ocn_fme_horiz_remap.F and mpas_seaice_fme_horiz_remap.F.

6. MPAS FILL VALUE LEAKAGE THROUGH SpMV [FIXED]
   - Was: depth-coarsened fields have fill values (1e34) at deep levels
     for shallow ocean cells. These leaked through the SpMV.
   - Fix: added abs(val) > 1e10 zeroing in MPAS-O and MPAS-SI send
     buffer packing, matching the EAM pattern.

